content: That's a great list! I'm particularly drawn to atmospheric and twisty stories, and 'The Witch Elm' seems to fit the bill. I've heard great things about Tana French's Dublin Murder Squad series, but I haven't read any of her standalone novels yet. Can you tell me more about 'The Witch Elm'? Is it similar to her Dublin Murder Squad books in terms of style and tone, or does it have a distinct feel?
